HEADWORD: Dinotherium
<hw>Di`no*the"ri*um</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>dinotherium</ets>,
fr. Gr. <grk>deino`s</grk> terrible + <grk>qhri`on</grk> beast.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A large extinct proboscidean mammal from the
miocene beds of Europe and Asia. It is remarkable for a pair of tusks
directed downward from the decurved apex of the lower jaw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

